<br>
No, the point of it is that for some, RP is intensely immersive.  Having someone /shout &quot;ur ghey, my uberness ownz joo!&quot; or variations on that disrupts their immersion even when the d00d is just shouting it in fun to his buddy across the zone.  RP'ers in EQ are looking for a server with a culture more supportive of immersion, where it's easier to get in-character and stay in-character.  I think FV has that.<br>
<br>
